<DESCRIPT>  FOOD; RECIPE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  As this sampler of recipes shows, flavorful walnuts add crunchy goodness to
salads, side dishes and desserts; SEARED BOSC PEARS  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Food  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  AH, NUTS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  WITH WALNUTS; 1 orange; 1 1/2 cups canned apricot nectar; 1 1/2 cup walnuts,
divided; 1 1/2 teaspoons honey; 3/4 cup plain non-fat yogurt; 3 ripe Bosc
pears; 1 tablespoon walnuts, finely chopped; 1 head red oak-leaf lettuce; 
Reserving orange, peel orange with vegetable peeler. Cut peel into thin strips
1 1/2 inches long. Simmer peel and 1/2 cup apricot nectar in saucepan over
medium-low heat. Stir often until nectar evaporates.;   In a food processor or
electric blender, puree 3/4 cup walnuts with honey and 2 tablespoons of orange
juice from the peeled orange.;   In a mixing bowl, combine yogurt with 1 cup
apricot nectar. Halve and core pears. Leaving skins on, cut into thin slices
so pears remain attached at the stem end. Fan out pear halves and brush with
apricot-yogurt mixture. Place pear fans, core side down, in a non-stick saute
pan. Sear over high heat until edges are slightly charred.;   Place 3
tablespoons apricot-yogurt mixture on center of each of 6 serving plates.
Rotate plates until yogurt is evenly distributed over each plate. Place 1
tablespoon orange-walnut mixture off-center on each plate.;   Place fan base
in center of orange-walnut mixture, so that pear fan rests, charred side up,
on apricot-yogurt mixture. Sprinkle orange rind and chopped walnuts onto
yogurt mixture. Garnish with red oak-leaf lettuce. Serves 6.;   -- From Maine
Chance spa resort in Phoenix; WALNUT COCONUT CHEWS; 1 1/4 cups all-purpose
flour; 1/2 cup sugar; 1/2 cup butter or margarine; 2 eggs; 1/2 cup firmly
packed brown sugar; 1 teaspoon vanilla; 1/8 teaspoon baking soda; 1 cup
chopped walnuts; 1/2 cup flaked coconut;  Heat oven to 350 degrees. Lightly
grease an 8-inch-square baking pan. Combine flour and sugar. Using a pastry
blender, fork or food processor, cut in butter until mixture resembles fine
meal. Press into greased pan. Bake for 20 minutes or just until edges are
lightly golden.;   Meanwhile, combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla; beat
well. Stir in baking soda, walnuts and coconut. Spoon over hot crust; spread
to cover evenly.;   Return to oven; bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or
until top is set. Cool completely. Cut into bars. Makes 18 bars.;  
Variations:;   Raspberry Walnut Chews -- Spread 1 1/4 cups raspberry jam over
hot crust. Top with walnut mixture, omitting coconut. Bake as directed.;  
Chocolate Nugget Chews -- Prepare crust as directed. To egg mixture, add 1/2
cup softened butter and 2/3 cup flour; mix well. Stir in baking soda, walnuts
and 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips, omitting coconut. Spread over hot crust.
Bake as directed.; COMPANY GREEN BEANS; 1 pound fresh green beans, ends
trimmed; Boiling, salted water; 1/3 cup walnut pieces; 2 tablespoons butter; 1
red bell pepper, cut into short strips; 3 green onions, thinly sliced; 1
teaspoon dried basil (or 1 tablespoon fresh); 1 garlic clove, minced; Salt and
pepper;  Cook whole, trimmed beans in a large amount of boiling, salted water
to cook the beans quickly. Cook uncovered to preserve bright green color. When
beans are tender-crisp, drain.;   Meanwhile, in a separate skillet, add
walnuts to melted butter. Cook over medium heat 1 minute, then stir in red
bell pepper strips; saute until pepper is tender-crisp. Stir in green onions,
basil and garlic. Saute briefly, stirring well. Combine drained beans with
walnut mixture and add salt and pepper as desired. Makes 4 servings.; GRILLED
BREAD WITH; WALNUTS AND GOAT CHEESE; 1 thick slice country bread; 1 clove
garlic, cut in half; 1 ounce fresh goat cheese, at room temperature; Meat of 2
freshly cracked walnuts, very coarsely chopped (about 1 tablespoon); Sea salt,
freshly ground pepper; Extra-virgin olive oil;  Grill bread on both sides.
Lightly rub one side with cut clove of garlic. Spread goat cheese over the
top. Sprinkle with walnuts. Season to taste with salt and pepper and drizzle
with few drops olive oil. Makes 1 serving.; GOLDEN BEETS; WITH WALNUTS; 1
bunch small to medium golden beets of uniform size; 2 to 3 tablespoons
extra-virgin olive oil; Balsamic vinegar; Salt, freshly ground pepper; 1/4 cup
very coarsely chopped walnuts; 2 tablespoons very coarsely chopped celery
leaves;  Trim beets of all but 1 inch of stem. Wrap tightly in foil. Bake at
400 degrees about 1 hour, or until beets are tender but firm. Test with wooden
skewer. Remove beets from foil. When cool enough to handle, peel and cut beets
into wedges.;   Place beets on platter and add olive oil, few drops balsamic
vinegar and season to taste with salt and pepper. Toss. Sprinkle with walnuts
and celery leaves. Toss again and serve. Makes 4 servings.; APPLES AND
ROASTED; WALNUTS; New-crop unshelled walnuts; Small, crisp apples;  Place
unshelled nuts in shallow pan. Roast at 400 degrees 12 to 15 minutes. Remove
from oven and transfer to bowl or platter. Serve immediately, accompanied by
apples.;   Note: There should be a handful of walnuts and 2 or 3 little apples
per person. Provide nutcrackers for the nuts and knives for the apples. Serve
at the end of a country-style meal or as a wonderfully satisfying afternoon
snack.; CARIBBEAN FUDGE PIE; 1/4 cup butter or margarine, softened; 3/4 cup
firmly packed brown sugar; 3 eggs; 1 12-ounce package semi-sweet chocolate
pieces, melted; 2 teaspoons instant coffee powder; 1 teaspoon rum extract (or
1 tablespoon dark rum); 1/4 cup all-purpose flour; 1 cup chopped walnuts; 1
9-inch unbaked pastry pie shell; 1/2 cup halves or large pieces walnuts; Heat
oven to 375 degrees. In large bowl, combine butter and brown sugar; beat until
light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate, instant coffee and rum extract to butter mixture; mix well.
Stir in flour and 1 cup chopped walnuts; pour into pie shell. Decorate top
with walnut pieces. Bake in lower third of oven for 25 minutes. Cool on wire
rack. Chill before serving. Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream, if
desired. Store in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.  </TEXT>
