DIABETICS -- AND DIETERS, TOO -- CAN SATISFY
THEIR SWEET TOOTH WITH THESE DESSERTS.  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>   1 stick 'lite' margarine;  8 packets Equal;   Dash of cinnamon;  3 eggs;  1/2
cup flour;  1 teaspoon vanilla;  1/2 teaspoon chocolate extract;   Cocoa
powder;   Whipped topping, optional;   Preheat oven to 325. Melt chocolate and
margarine. Add Equal, cinnamon, eggs, flour, vanilla and chocolate extract,
beating until smooth. Spray an 8-inch glass pie pan with non-stick spray; dust
with cocoa. Pour mixture in; bake 10 to 12 minutes. (The center will be
runny.) Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Serve with whipped topping, if
desired. Makes 6 servings. Diabetic exchange per serving: 1 starch, 2 1/2
fats.;    -- Dallas Morning News;     PINEAPPLE CREAM; 1  cup canned,
unsweetened pineapple chunks, drained; 8 ounces unsweetened evaporated skim
milk;   Juice of 1 lime; 1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract; 1 envelope
unflavored gelatin; 2 tablespoons cold water; 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind;  
Reserve 4 tablespoons pineapple chunks for topping. In blender, combine
remaining pineapple chunks, milk, lime juice and vanilla extract and puree in
blender. Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a cup. Let stand a few minutes to
gel and then place cup in a bowl of hot water to dissolve. Remove, let cool,
and add to pineapple mixture, blending. Mix in lemon rind and pour into
dessert dishes. Refrigerate or place in freezer until set. Garnish with
reserved pineapple chunks. Serves 4.; -- From "International Menu; Diabetic
Cookbook" by Betty; Marks &amp; Lucille Haley; Schechter (Contemporary; Books,
Inc., $14.95).;  APPLE CRISP;  Vegetable spray; 4-5 apples, peeled, cored, and
sliced; 2 tablespoons raisins;  1/4 cup rolled oats; 1 tablespoon wheat germ; 
1/4 cup Grape Nuts; 1 tablespoon ground cinnamon;  1/4 teaspoon ground cloves;
 1/4 teaspoon freshly grated nutmeg; 2 tablespoons sunflower seeds; 1
tablespoon sunflower seed oil;  1/2 cup apple juice;  1/2 cup part-skim
ricotta cheese (optional);   Lightly coat a 9- by 12-inch baking dish with
vegetable spray. Line pan with sliced apples. Mix together all other
ingredients except apple juice and cheese and spread over apples. Slowly
drizzle apple juice over crust and set aside 15 minutes. Preheat oven to 350
and bake crisp 25 to 30 minutes until crust is brown. If desired, serve with a
dab of ricotta cheese. Serves 6; -- From "International Menu; Diabetic
Cookbook" by Betty; Marks &amp; Lucille Haley; Schechter (Contemporary; Books,
Inc., $14.95).;  BANANA CREAM PIE;  Crust; 2 cups graham cracker crumbs;  1/2
cup diet margarine, melted;   Banana Filling; 1 envelope unflavored gelatin; 1
cup skim milk;  3/4 cup part-skim ricotta cheese; 2 teaspoons vanilla extract;
4 packets Equal; 3 medium fresh bananas, peeled and sliced;   Topping; 2 egg
whites; 5 packets Equal;  Nutmeg, if desired;   Crust: Blend ingredients.
Press crust over bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan. Bake in preheated 350
oven 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.;    Filling: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup milk in
small saucepan. Let soften 5 minutes. Heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves,
about 3 minutes. In food processor, blend ricotta cheese until smooth; add
gelatin mixture, remaining milk and vanilla. Blend until smooth. Reserve 1
cup. Add 4 packets Equal and 2 sliced bananas to remaining mixture in
processor. Blend until smooth. Place remaining sliced banana on bottom of
graham cracker crust. Pour banana cream mixture over banana slices. Chill 1
hour.;    Topping: Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 5 packets Equal,
beating until stiff peaks form. Fold into reserved ricotta cheese mixture.
Spoon over pie filling. Chill 4-6 hours. Sprinkle with nutmeg before serving.
Makes 8 servings. Diabetic exchange: 1/2 non-fat milk, 1 fruit, 1 bread, 2
fat.; -- "Equal Fruitful Desserts";  POACHED PEARS WITH; CHOCOLATE SAUCE; 4
cups sun-sweetened apple juice; 1 teaspoon lemon juice; 1 cinnamon stick; 6
fresh pears, pared and cored; 1 cinnamon stick;  1/3 cup evaporated skim milk;
3 squares (1 ounce each) unsweetened baking chocolate, coarsely chopped; 1
tablespoon corn starch; 1 tablespoon unsweetened apple juice; 30 packets
Equal;   Pears: Combine apple juice, lemon juice and cinnamon stick. Bring to
a boil. Add pears and reheat to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer 15 to 20 minutes
or until pears are tender. Cool. Remove pears and set aside. Reserve 1 cup
poaching liquid.;    Sauce: Combine reserved 1 cup poaching liquid and
cinnamon stick. Boil; reduce heat and simmer. Cook until liquid reduced to 1/2
cup, about 10 to 15 minutes. Remove cinnamon stick; reserve liquid. In double
boiler, over low heat, melt chocolate with milk. In separate bowl, blend corn
starch and apple juice; add to chocolate. Stir constantly over low heat until
thickens. Stir in poaching liquid; blend until smooth. Remove from heat; stir
in Equal. Place pears on dessert plates and drizzle with chocolate sauce.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings, 1 pear and 3 tablespoons sauce per
serving. Diabetic exchange: 2 fruit, 2 bread, 1 1/2 fat.; -- "Equal Fruitful
Desserts";  TANGERINE CHEESECAKE;  Crust; 2 cups graham cracker crumbs;  1/2
cup diet margarine, melted;   Tangerine Filling; 12 ounces low-calorie cream
cheese; 1 cup part-skim ricotta cheese; 12 packets Equal; 1 envelope
unflavored gelatin; 1 cup tangerine juice; 1 packet low-calorie whipped
topping mix;  1/2 cup skim milk; 1 cup peeled, seeded and chopped fresh
tangerines (about 2); 1 fresh tangerine, peeled and sectioned, if desired;  
Crust: Blend crust ingredients and press over bottom and half way up sides of
9-inch spring form pan sprayed with non-stick vegetable spray. Bake in
preheated 350 oven 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.;    Filling: Blend cream cheese and
ricotta cheese. Add Equal. In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over tangerine
juice. Let soften 1 minute. Heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin
dissolves, about 3 minutes. Prepare whipped topping according to package
directions, substituting milk for water. Add gelatin mixture to cheese
mixture; blend until smooth. Fold whipped topping into cheese mixture. Stir in
chopped tangerine pieces. Spoon into crust and spread evenly. Chill 4 to 6
hours. Garnish with tangerine sections. Makes one 9-inch cheesecake or 16
servings, 1 slice per serving. Diabetic exchange: 1/2 non-fat milk, 1 fruit, 1
1/2 fat.; -- "Equal Fruitful Desserts"  </TEXT>
